definition: elder/term of respect for a Buddhist monk

prefix used before the surname of a person or a numeral indicating the order of birth of the children in a family or to indicate affection or familiarity/old (of people)/venerable (person)/experienced/of long standing/always/all the time/of the past/very/outdated/(of meat etc) tough

sentences.english: New Presbyter is but old Priest with large.

sentences.english: But Elisha sat in his house, and the elders sat with him;
sentences.chinese: 那時，以利沙正坐在家中，長老也與他同坐。

sentences.english: 17From Miletus, Paul sent to Ephesus for the elders of the church.
sentences.chinese: 保羅從米利都打發人往以弗所去，請教會的長老來。

sentences.english: There was a wedding recently, at Fairview presbyterian church.
sentences.chinese: 最近，在美景鎮的長老會教堂，舉行了一場婚禮。

sentences.english: I am a therapist at columbia-presbyterian.
sentences.chinese: 我在哥倫比亞的長老派教會醫院當醫師。

sentences.english: And the king sent, and they gathered unto him all the elders of Judah and of Jerusalem.
sentences.chinese: 王差遣人招聚猶大和耶路撒冷的衆長老來。

sentences.english: There are still two Presbyterian bodies in Ireland that are Unitarian .
sentences.chinese: 還有兩個長老機構在愛爾蘭的統一。

sentences.chinese: 第一長老教會在必新澤西。

sentences.english: So Master Sugehara named his temple "The Date Monastery".
sentences.chinese: 長老遂把自己住持的寺院更名爲棗寺。

sentences.english: Elder Lee will be preaching next week.
sentences.chinese: 下主日李席舟長老將傳講信息請代禱。

sentences.english: But the chief priests and elders persuaded the multitude that they should ask Barabbas, and destroy Jesus.
sentences.chinese: 祭司長和長老，挑唆衆人，求釋放巴拉巴，除滅耶穌。

sentences.english: The Elders have killed the 40 sons, and here is proof.
sentences.chinese: 長老們已經殺了40個亞哈族的兒子，這些就是證明。

sentences.english: The elder unto the wellbeloved Gaius, whom I love in the truth.
sentences.chinese: 作長老的寫信給親愛的該猶，就是我誠心所愛的。

sentences.english: Then David and the elders, clothed in sackcloth, fell facedown.
sentences.chinese: 大衛和長老都身穿麻衣，面伏於地。

sentences.english: The family had approached the local MLA for help.
sentences.chinese: 這個家庭曾經尋求地方長老會的幫助。

definition: one who has mastered the sutras (Buddhism)
senior male fellow student or apprentice/son (older than oneself) of one's teacher
used for 師傅|师傅 (in Taiwan)/master/qualified worker
founder (of a craft, religious sect etc)
abbr. for 眾議院|众议院[Zhong4 yi4 yuan4], House of Representatives
